From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: emscripten-forge patcher <patch@emscripten-forge>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Remove annoy static library to fix duplicate PyInit_annoylib on Emscripten/wasm32

annoymodule.cc is compiled twice under the current meson.build:

  1. Into the intermediate static library libannoycore.a (via annoy_static)
  2. Directly into the annoylib extension module (via its 'sources' list)

When the extension module links against libannoycore.a (via 'link_with'),
the Emscripten/wasm32 toolchain reports a hard linker error:

  wasm-ld: error: duplicate symbol: PyInit_annoylib
  >>> defined in libannoycore.a(annoymodule.cc.o)
  >>> defined in annoylib.cpython-312-wasm32-emscripten.so(annoymodule.cc.o)

Root cause: annoymodule.cc is the Python module entry point
(PyInit_annoylib).  It must appear in exactly one translation unit
that becomes the final .so.  Placing it in a static library and also
compiling it directly into the extension produces two definitions of
the same symbol, which POSIX linkers silently discard but Emscripten's
wasm-ld treats as a hard error.

Fix: remove the annoy_core_sources list and the annoy_static
static_library() definition entirely; set 'link_with' to an empty list
in the extension metadata.  annoymodule.cc is already compiled directly
into the extension via its 'sources' entry, so the static library was
entirely redundant.

This change is safe on all other targets: native and GHCR builds are
unaffected because the extension never needed the static library to
resolve any symbols that were not already being compiled in via sources.

Affected files
  scikitplot/cexternals/_annoy/meson.build  (linker error)
---
 scikitplot/cexternals/_annoy/meson.build | 19 +------------------
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 18 deletions(-)

diff --git a/scikitplot/cexternals/_annoy/meson.build b/scikitplot/cexternals/_annoy/meson.build
--- a/scikitplot/cexternals/_annoy/meson.build
+++ b/scikitplot/cexternals/_annoy/meson.build
@@ -222,22 +222,6 @@
 message('Final compile args: ' + ' '.join(extra_compile_args))
 message('Final link args: ' + ' '.join(extra_link_args))
 
-annoy_core_sources = [
-  # 'src/annoyluamodule.cc',  # (Lua binding)
-  'src/annoymodule.cc',  # (Python binding)
-]
-
-annoy_static = static_library(
-  'annoycore',
-  annoy_core_sources,
-  include_directories: inc_dir_annoy,
-  dependencies: dep_list,
-  cpp_args: cython_cpp_flags + extra_compile_args,
-  link_args: extra_link_args,
-  install: false
-  # install_dir: np_dir / 'random/lib',
-)
-
 ######################################################################
 ## extension metadata
 ######################################################################
@@ -263,10 +247,7 @@
       inc_dir_py,
     ],
     'dependencies': dep_list,                     # External libraries and dependencies
-    'link_with': [                                # Link with the created static library
-      # version_link_args
-      annoy_static,
-    ],
+    'link_with': [],                              # No static library: avoids duplicate PyInit_annoylib on Emscripten/wasm32
     'override_options': [
       # 'cython_language=c',                        # Ensure Cython knows to generate C code
       'cython_language=cpp',                        # Ensure Cython knows to generate C code
